Live Threat Hunt with Security Onion + ELK
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Deploy and configure Security Onion components for network security monitoring
Integrate ELK Stack for centralized log analysis and visualization
Perform live threat hunting using Suricata IDS and custom detection rules
Create automated threat detection scripts using Python and Elasticsearch API
Generate security dashboards and reports for incident response
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of networking fundamentals (TCP/IP, ports, protocols)
Familiarity with log analysis concepts
Elementary Python programming skills
Basic cybersecurity knowledge
Lab Environment
Al Nafi Cloud Machine Setup: This lab runs on a single Ubuntu 20.04 LTS cloud machine with 8GB RAM and 100GB storage. Click Start Lab to access your pre-configured environment. No additional VM setup required.

Task 1: Deploy Security Onion Components with Docker
Step 1: Install Docker and Docker Compose
# Update system and install prerequisites
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y curl wget git vim net-tools

# Install Docker
